<main class="container">
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">Items Offered <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p><b>Q1:</b> What items can I purchase from Chimelle Shop?</p>
            <p><b>A:</b> Chimelle Shop offers a variety of K-pop merchandise, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Albums:</b> CD, DVD, LP, and CD-QR versions</li>
                <li><b>Merchandise:</b> Concert official merchandise and other official K-pop goods</li>
                <li><b>Lightsticks:</b> Concert official lightsticks</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
<div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">Album Press <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p><b>Q2:</b> What does "album press" mean?</p>
            <p><b>A:</b> Album press refers to the production period of a CD album, which depends on when it was purchased in South Korea. Chimelle Shop offers two types of album press:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>First-Press:</b> Albums or merchandise purchased during the pre-order period or first-time release.</li>
                <li><b>Restock:</b> Albums or merchandise repurchased after the pre-order period or initial release.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">Item Availability <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p><b>Q3:</b> What does "availability" mean for an item?</p>
            <p><b>A:</b> Item availability is categorized as follows:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Pre-order:</b> The item is not yet released, in our KR warehouse, on board, or undergoing customs clearance.</li>
                <li><b>On Hand:</b> The item is in our PH warehouse and ready to be packed and shipped to customers.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">Pre-Order Information <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p><b>Q4:</b> How long do pre-ordered items take to arrive?</p>
            <p><b>A:</b> Pre-ordered items usually take 3-4 weeks to reach our PH warehouse. Please note that all items are imported and must comply with Philippine customs clearance standards.</p>
            <p><b>Q5:</b> What are "pre-order benefits"?</p>
            <p><b>A:</b> Pre-order benefits are additional inclusions provided to customers who purchase during the pre-order period. These benefits include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>First-Press Benefits:</b> Exclusive items such as posters or photocard sets, which are included with albums bought during the pre-order period.</li>
                <li class="sub-item">Albums with separate posters include a complimentary poster tube.</li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Pre-Order Benefits (POB):</b> Special inclusions offered by selected stores like Makestar, WITHMUU, and Weverse Shop. These benefits vary and may include photo cards, postcards, or stamps.</li>
                <li class="sub-item">Note: Albums with pre-order benefits may not include first-press benefits.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h2 class="faq-question">Authenticity of Items <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h2>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p><b>Q6:</b> How can I verify if an album I purchased is official?</p>
            <p><b>A:</b> To verify if an album is official, check the barcode or the KOMCA sticker on the back of the album. Keep in mind that KOMCA stickers have evolved over time, so their appearance may differ depending on the release year.</p>
            <p><b>Q7:</b> How can I confirm if the merchandise I purchased is authentic?</p>
            <p><b>A:</b> You can confirm the authenticity of merchandise by checking the back of its packaging for the certification sticker issued by the artist's agency.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
